# Visual And Copy Standards

- Use executive language: short, concrete, outcome-driven. Avoid beginner AI education language.
- Prioritize clarity over decoration. Gradients, glass cards, memes, and motion must support the message.
- Keep CTAs focused: run the 3-minute check, then go to the full PromptAnatomy system.
- Use memes as visual breaks only; do not let them dominate the page.
- For every new visual section, check mobile order: headline, value, CTA or useful visual.
- Keep the color system premium and restrained: dark base, white text, cyan/blue accent.
- When adding images, prefer SVG for diagrams and AVIF/WebP for screenshots; define dimensions or aspect ratio.
